    "summary": "I am an expert in the development of National Practice Guidelines in mental health. I have extended knowledge on Mental Health and Addiction topics. I am a researcher (PhD), always focussing on the quality of care for people in need of mental health/addiction care.\n\nI worked as a mental health nurse in a Dutch addiction treatment centre (1987 - 2000). After this I worked as a research associate on projects linking mental health issues and addiction. Ever since I am involved in the topic of ADHD and Substance Abuse.\nStarting in 2005 I initiated an international research network, aiming at:\n1) Prevention of development of Substance Abuse in children/adolescents with ADHD\n2) Enhancement of procedures for diagnoses and treatment of adolescents and adults with both disorders.\nThis network is a formal foundation since September 2010. You can find information on the ICASA Foundation via\nwww.adhdandsubstanceabuse.org\n\nIn 2016-2018 I served as a senior advisor for the Netherlands Ministry of Health, setting up structure and infrastructure for development of National Practice Guidelines in the field of people with learning disabilities. For the result, go to https://www6.erasmusmc.nl/richtlijnontwikkeling-vg/6252108/mjp_sv  (publication in Dutch). In this project I collaborated with national consumer organizations, and national professional organizations.\n\nSpecialties: \nResearch on ADHD and Substance Abuse;\nDevelopment and maintenance of an international network;\nDevelopment of National Practice Guidelines.",
